# GitHub Workflow Conventions

## Validation

When editing workflow files, ensure:

- Valid YAML syntax
- Required top-level keys: `name`, `on`, `jobs`
- Every job has a `runs-on` field
- Action versions are pinned (e.g., `actions/checkout@v4`, not `@main`)

## Key Workflows

| Workflow | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `client-build.yml` | Client build pipeline |
| `server-build.yml` | Server build pipeline |
| `ci-test-limited.yml` | CI test suite |
| `client-unit-tests.yml` | Client unit tests |
| `server-integration-tests.yml` | Server integration tests |

## Testing Locally Before Push

```bash
# Server
cd app/server && mvn spotless:check          # Formatting
cd app/server && mvn test                    # Unit tests

# Client
cd app/client && yarn lint                   # ESLint
cd app/client && yarn prettier               # Prettier
cd app/client && yarn test:unit              # Jest
cd app/client && yarn check-types            # TypeScript
```
